	<text>
		<body>
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001043_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 13 top left--><!--hand 02 68011 superscript C top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">17<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> June</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> Haldane</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I am informed 
<lb/>this morning by 
<lb/><persName>Prof. Daubeny</persName> of 
<lb/>Oxford that it is 
<lb/>intended to confer 
<lb/>an Honorary degree 
<lb/>upon me on 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001043_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>the 24<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> the day 
<lb/>which you had 
<lb/>appointed us to 
<lb/>come to your 
<lb/>house and it 
<lb/>would scarcely do 
<lb/>to ask the University 
<lb/>to put off its annual 
<lb/>meeting for conferring 
<lb/>degrees I am obliged 
<lb/>to trust to your 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001043_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>good nature to 
<lb/>make your 
<lb/>invitation for 
<lb/>the 25<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi>. I am 
<lb/>to go down to 
<lb/>Oxford on the 
<lb/>23<hi rend="sup underline">d</hi> I hope this 
<lb/>will not put you 
<lb/>to any inconvenience 
<lb/>The degree is only 
<lb/>a mark of approbation 
<lb/>conferred for 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001043_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/>distinguished services 
<lb/>or attainments and 
<lb/>though I would 
<lb/>rather continue at 
<lb/>my book my friends 
<lb/>think I should 
<lb/>accept it and 
<lb/>I imagine you 
<lb/>will not object 
<lb/>to postponing the 
<lb/>invitation</p>
<lb/><p>Excuse my 
<lb/>troubling you thus 
<lb/>&amp; believe me yours</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p> <addSpan spanTo="#p1-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left margin of p. 1'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p>If the proposal is quite inconvenient 
<lb/>I would try &amp; come up to you in the evening</p><anchor xml:id="p1-01"/>
			
</div>
